eNCA reporter Govan Whittles is checking the impact for us and joins us live. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will implement Stage 4 load-shedding from 3pm to 10pm on Wednesday. The power utility says this is due to a spike in demand. READ: SA sees worst power cuts on record in 2020, research shows "Eskom regrets to announce that load-shedding will move from Stage 2 to Stage 4 at 15:00 until 22:00 tonight, due to exceptionally high demand," read the statement from Eskom. Eskom is urging customers to use electricity sparingly. #POWERALERT 1
